-- UN Mission Head in Darfur ‘Saddened’ at Loss of Sudan Delegation
-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 2012-08-19T15:49:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-19/un-mission-head-in-darfur-saddened-at-loss-of-sudan-delegation.html
Aichatou Mindaoudou, acting head of
the  United Nations ’ Mission in Darfur, is “saddened” after a
delegation led by Sudan’s Minister of Guidance and Endowments
Ghazi Al-Saddiq was killed in an air crash.  The crash, which also claimed the crew, happened near
Talodi, in the district of South Kordofan, UNAMID said in a
statement today.  “Ms. Mindaoudou offers her deepest sympathies and
heartfelt condolences to the bereaved families of all victims
and to the government and the people of Sudan,” UNAMID said in
the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  